I should probably clarify why I dislike CDs. First, price, but there are ways around that. Second, it's straight up retarded to use them as a distribution mechanism. Don't put bits on plastic, then put plastic in boxes, then put boxes in stores, pay for people to work the stores, pay for security, install annoying anti-theft devices that take me an hour to cut through without a chainsaw, and then expect me to go to the store and buy the product just so I can take it home and pull the bits off before throwing the plastic away. Just give me the goddamn bits directly over the wire and we're all happier. Easier for me, cheaper for you. And I expect that reduction in distribution costs to be passed partially to me in the form of cheaper-than-retail downloads.
<br />

<br />
I'd feel the same way about DVDs if there was any way to get that much data across the wire cheaply (and there will be in a few years). Until then purchase of DVDs is fine. I'll have them archived long before they ever decay.
