<br />

<br />
<a href="http://www.bittorrent.com/introduction.html" target="_blank" class="postlink">Bittorrent</a> was originally written not to pirate materials, but to nullify the costs of distribution (a much more dangerous idea). BT's goal is to give everyone the ability to broadcast anything to everyone. That spells @#%$.e.d in big media terms. Copyright isn't the whole issue.
<br />

<br />
Of course, the two ideas fit rather naturally together, despite arising from different needs.<br />
