			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"> Depends on the industry as well, we might be gaining some but a few industries are still getting hurt.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I wont do it myself.  I stopped buying as albums phased out.  That joke in MiB about having to buy the "White Album" again was un-funny to me. Mostly I just got tired of Horrible Musicians wowing me with one song and having a disc full of @#%$ to go with it.  Sharing audio with people got me back into buying CDs.
<br />

<br />
The music industry has floated ultra high profits because of advances in information science.  There was no music industry before their were recordings. Recordings killed the sheet music industry.  And sheet music transformed music from the performance market that preceeded it.
<br />

<br />
Their current channel  is now dead.  They need to find new ways of selling their craft, the idea of selling copies of performances is now moot because of the same trends in advances that boosted their profits has made their channel obsolete.  This battle is about that industry coming to terms with that.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
